'''
ChatBot is programmed to respond to user input in a friendly and engaging manner. It uses Natural Language Toolkit and the ChatterBot library to generate responses.


CreatePersonality(name):

  Description: Creates a chatbot instance with a specific name and personality.
  Arguments:
  name (str): The name of the chatbot.
  Returns:
  chatbot: ChatBot instance with the specified name and personality.

ReadInput(user_input):

  Description: Processes user input using NLTK for more processing.
  Arguments:
  user_input (str): The input provided by the user.
  Returns:
  tokens (list of str): Tokenized user input.

GenerateResponse(chatbot, user_input):

  Description: Generates a response based on user input using the provided chatbot instance.
  Arguments:
  chatbot: ChatBot instance created using CreatePersonality().
  user_input (str): The input provided by the user.
  Returns:
  response (str): The generated response.

    
Examples:

chatbot = CreatePersonality("SarcasticBot")

user_input = "Tell me a joke"
tokens = ReadInput(user_input)

response = GenerateResponse(chatbot, user_input)

Enjoy your jokes!
'''
